  <title>carboxylic acids</title>
  <termversion>2.3.3</termversion>
  <lastupdated>2014-02-24</lastupdated>
  <definitions>
    <item>
      <id>1</id>
      <text>Oxoacids having the structure RC(=O)OH. The term is used as a suffix in systematic name formation to denote the –C(=O)OH group including its carbon atom.</text>
